1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with Physical Layer Security (PLS) and outage probability of achievable secrecy rate, which are key concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless sensor networks and their communication protocols, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with secrecy and eavesdropping, which are key concepts in cryptography and security. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses sensor scheduling to enhance PLS, which is a control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although less likely, the paper does involve wireless communication and signal processing, which are relevant to multimedia applications.
